FAA set to award $ 1 billion air - traffic contract . The Federal Aviation Administration said Friday that it would announce on Monday the award of an almost $ 1 billion contract involving the modernization of the U . S . air - traffic control system . The FAA did not identify the contract to be awarded , but industry specialists said it was likely to be to modernize the radar approach system that handles aircraft within some 50 miles of airports . Competing for the so - called standard terminal - automation replacement system ( STARS ) contract are Lockheed Martin Corp , Boeing Co and Raytheon Co . 
